slides.speakerNotes:
Transition from Week 1
&quot;Last week, you discovered something about yourself.&quot;
&quot;You imagined the life you want to build.&quot;
&quot;You created your dream board.&quot;
Pause.
&quot;But a dream by itself is not yet a business.&quot;

&quot;Don't explain insurance.&quot;
&quot;Just become curious.&quot;
Ask them:
&quot;Is this really your biggest concern?&quot;
&quot;Tell me more.&quot;
&quot;Why is this important?&quot;
&quot;What have you already tried?&quot;
&quot;What happens if nothing changes?&quot;
Pause.
&quot;If five more people tell you the same thing...&quot;
&quot;...you're no longer guessing.&quot;
&quot;You're building your business on evidence.&quot;
Finish with:
&quot;Next week, we'll transform your validated problem into your Financial Entrepreneurship Canvas—and you'll begin designing a business that creates real value for the people you've chosen to serve.&quot;
